## ¬ß4. CHRONIC ILLNESS & DISABILITY WORLDWIDE

- Flexible participation, async options  
- Physical accessibility: ramps, ergonomics  
- Spoon Theory: plan energy units  
- Flow: pacing for long COVID or chronic fatigue

---

## ¬ß5. OTHER NEURODIVERGENT CONDITIONS

- **Dyslexia:** Multi-lingual challenges; use audio, fonts  
- **OCD:** Structured routines, no compulsion  
- **Tourette‚Äôs:** Normalize tics  
- **Bipolar:** Flexible schedules, support low phases, celebrate high-phase creativity  
- **SPD:** Sensory kits, weighted blankets, ear protection  

---

## ¬ß6. INTERSECTIONALITY & GLOBAL CONTEXTS

- Neurodivergence + culture + class + gender + geography + migration  
- Code-switching, cultural translation, boundary setting  
- Center Global South, decolonize discourse  
- Elder nodes: extra patience for age-related neurodivergence  

---

## ¬ß7. NEURODIVERGENT CHILDREN IN DIFFERENT CULTURES

- Cultural child-rearing: individualistic vs. collectivist vs. indigenous  
- Education: formal/informal, play-based, inclusive  
- Family: nuclear/extended, co-parenting, Body Doubling  

---

## ¬ß8. COMMON PITFALLS ACROSS CULTURES

- Assumption: Western methods universal  
- Ignoring local stigma/resources  
- Toxic positivity ‚Üí listen  
- Inspiration porn ‚Üí validate existence  

---

## ¬ß9. PRINCIPLE: ADAPTATION, NOT ASSIMILATION

- ADHD: environment adapts  
- Autism: authenticity + cultural navigation  
- Trauma: culturally defined safety  
- Chronic illness: rest integrated  
- Motto: *‚ÄúYour culture is not your enemy; oppressive systems are.‚Äù*

